President Barack Obama wrote a letter to the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President Pro Tempore of the Senate on September 23, 2014. In the letter, he stated that U.S. Armed Forces were conducting operations against al-Qa'ida and associated forces in various locations. He informed them that, on his direction, U.S. military forces had started a series of strikes in Syria against the Khorasan Group, which is a part of al-Qa'ida. He justified these strikes as necessary to defend the United States and its allies. President Obama stated that he had authorized these actions based on his constitutional and statutory authority as Commander in Chief and Chief Executive, as well as his authority to conduct foreign relations. He mentioned that he was providing this report to keep Congress informed, in accordance with the War Powers Resolution. The President expressed his appreciation for the Congress's support in this matter.